        "content": "\n**Untested entirely.** Highest-risk module ‚Äî it's the persistence/dedup layer; a bug silently drops or duplicates jobs.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Fresh DB creation, schema, and idempotent re-open (migration path for pre-`salary_range` DBs)\n- `diff()`: new job inserted ‚Üí in `new`; unchanged job ‚Üí neither list, `last_seen` bumped; changed content ‚Üí in `changed`, row updated\n- `diff()` called twice in a row with identical input ‚Üí second call returns `([], [])`\n- `next_seq()` ‚Äî starts at 1, increments monotonically, survives close/reopen\n- `next_seq()` concurrency claim ‚Äî `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` guarantees no duplicate ids under concurrent callers (integration-level, threads or subprocesses)\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta` ‚Äî missing key ‚Üí `None`; upsert overwrite via `ON CONFLICT`\n- `added_since()` ‚Äî strict `>` boundary (row at exactly `ts` excluded), ordering by `first_seen, company, title`\n- `count()` on empty vs populated DB\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) closes connection\n\n```python\n",
