        "title": "7. `agent.py` ‚Äî CLI helpers",
        "content": "\n**Untested entirely.** The pure-logic pieces (`cmd_db_new` filtering/truncation, `_normalize_ats`) are cheap to test; PDF rendering needs a subprocess mock (don't shell out to real Chrome in CI).\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run window (`marker is None` ‚Üí uses `since_days`); `--posted-days` filter with dated/undated split; `--dated-only` drops undated; group-boundary truncation (never splits a `first_seen` group mid-way, even if it exceeds `--limit`); `watermark` output is the *last kept group's* timestamp, not `now`\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now` sets current time; explicit watermark validated as ISO (invalid ‚Üí exit code 2, stderr message); neither `--now` nor watermark ‚Üí exit code 2\n- `cmd_report_num`: sequential zero-padded output (`\"001\"`, `\"002\"`)\n- `_normalize_ats`: each replacement rule (em-dash, smart quotes, ellipsis, zero-width, nbsp, arrows, bullet, currency symbols); replacements do NOT apply inside `<style>`/`<script>` blocks or inside tag attributes (only text nodes); counts dict accuracy\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file ‚Üí exit 2; Chrome not found ‚Üí `sys.exit`; Chrome produces non-PDF output ‚Üí exit 1 with stderr tail; temp `.ats.html` file cleaned up even on failure (the `finally`)\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env var takes precedence when it exists; falls through `shutil.which` candidates; falls through hardcoded macOS app paths; exits when none found\n- `main()`: subcommand dispatch (`db-new`, `db-mark`, `pdf-render`, `report-num`, `-h`/`--help`); bare invocation ‚Üí interactive; `-i`/`--interactive` flag forces interactive even with mode words; mode-word/flag split logic (`for i, t in enumerate(words): if t.startswith(\"-\")`)\n\n```python\n",
