        "title": "Integration-test gaps (nothing exercises cross-module flow today)",
        "content": "\n1. **End-to-end pipeline against mocked HTTP**: `respx`-mock two ATS endpoints, run `pipeline.run()` against a `tmp_path` DB, assert final job counts and DB state ‚Äî the seam between `fetch_all` ‚Üí `filter_jobs` ‚Üí `Store.diff` ‚Üí `dispatch` has zero coverage.\n2. **Re-run idempotency**: run the pipeline twice with identical fetch data; second run must report `new=0, changed=0`.\n3. **Scan-marker lifecycle** (`agent.py db-new` ‚Üí `db-mark`): simulate a pipeline run inserting rows, then `db-new` dump, then `db-mark <watermark>`, then a second `db-new` confirming previously-dumped rows aren't repeated.\n4. **Notifier failure isolation in a real dispatch call**: one notifier (e.g., SMS with bad creds) failing must not prevent console output ‚Äî currently only testable in isolation, not verified as a system property.\n5. **Concurrent pipeline workers against the same `jobs.db`** ‚Äî your own memory flags this as a known risk (`jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions`); no test guards against regression here.\n\n---\n\n",
